remarks: At pt 3, 'EF' = expansive stand of eastern red cedar. Avg 5.5m tall and ~40% canopy cover over 50m radius. 88 RSHA called persistently for ~2 min. Definitely not BLJA mimicry.
DOWO PT 2 min 5 'O' was the sound of tapping while foraging. ID'd by call.

88 GHOW flushed from roosting tree 19m from pt 6. Lots of whitewash indicates tree is used regularly. Pt 6 low bird count| but presence of RTHA persistently calling agitatedly from 34m and GHOW roost at 19m justifies low singbird presence.
